{"key":"post-12784263","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>12784263</id>\n<content>If you're going to boil after the soak(as you should), then anything between four hours and just before it starts to stink is fine.&amp;nbsp; The grains rarely get rancid within 24 hours, so I consider that the outside limit.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;I think 'germinating the endospores' is over-rated even though in the past I've sang that tune myself.&amp;nbsp; What I'm finding from additional experience is that simply hydrating the endospores makes then susceptible to getting killed in the pressure cooker, while dry endospores often survive the PC.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;I think part of the maturity process that is lacking in science(and politics) is being able to say some of the positions we previously held were wrong, and based on further study/knowledge we now believe such-and-such.&amp;nbsp; It would sure be refreshing to hear politicians follow that line of thought and tell those who accuse them of flip-flopping to blow it out their ass. &lt;img style=&quot;max-width:192px;height:auto;&quot; src=&quot;https://files.shroomery.org/smileys/lol.gif&quot; alt=&quot;:lol:&quot; title=&quot;:lol:&quot;/&gt;&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next></next>\n<prev>12784247</prev>\n<first>12784121</first>\n<last>12784263</last>\n<when>1277230058</when>\n<utime>06/22/10 09:07 PM</utime>\n</post>"}